# Coder Workspace Template

Remote development environment for **{{ business.company }}** powered by [Coder](https://coder.com).

## Prerequisites

- Running Coder instance (see [SETUP.md](./SETUP.md) or use `{{ pm.run }} tool devenv deploy`)
- [Coder CLI](https://coder.com/docs/install) installed
- `kubectl` access to the k3s cluster

## Quick Start

### Push the template

```sh
coder templates push {{ kebabCase business.company }} --directory .coder/
```

### Create a workspace

```sh
coder create my-workspace --template {{ kebabCase business.company }}
```

### Connect

```sh
coder open my-workspace
```

Or visit the Coder web UI directly.

## What's Included

- **Node.js** {{ versions.node }}
- **{{ pm.name }}** {{ versions.packageManager }}
- All system tools from `mise.toml` (caddy, mkcert, terraform, cloudflared, etc.)
- VSCode extensions from `.vscode/extensions.json`
- Port forwarding for all dev proxy ports
- Persistent storage via Kubernetes PVC

## Daily Workflow

1. Open Coder dashboard in browser
2. Click your workspace → VS Code opens in browser
3. Start dev proxy: `{{ pm.run }} dev:proxy`
4. Code, commit, push from the terminal
5. Close the browser tab when done
6. Workspace auto-stops after 30 minutes idle
7. Reopen later — picks up exactly where you left off

## Updating

When `resist.config.ts` changes:

```sh
{{ pm.run }} tool sync
{{ pm.run }} tool devenv push
```

Existing workspaces update when you click "Update" in the Coder dashboard.

